%5Cn%3Cp%3EStatistics%20don%E2%80%99t%20lie.%20Two%20Lok%20Sabha%20routs%2C%20losing%20forty%20of%20the%20previous%20fifty-one%20state%20assembly%20elections%2C%20tells%20a%20gloomy%20tale.%20The%20party%2C%20founded%20by%20A.O.%20Hume%20in%201885%2C%20needed%20to%20look%20at%20the%20French%20presidential%20elections%20of%20April%202022%20for%20a%20serious%20wake-up%20call.%20The%20two%20titanic%20parties%20who%20repeatedly%20formed%20the%20Parisian%20government%2C%20the%20Socialists%20and%20the%20Republicans%2C%20have%20nearly%20vanished%20amidst%20the%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20phenomenon%20(his%20party%2C%20Renaissance%2C%20is%20just%20six%20years%20old).%C2%A0Marine%20Le%20Pen%2C%20a%20right-wing%20ultranationalist%20is%20the%20dominant%20voice%20of%20the%20disgruntled%20Opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20395px)%2085vw%2C%20395px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1.jpg%20781w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1-195x300.jpg%20195w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1-666x1024.jpg%20666w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697623%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22607%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E2024%3A%20India%20in%20Free%20Fall%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Sanjay%20Jha.%20Publisher%3A%20Harper%20Collins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20faces%20not%20just%20a%20strong%20BJP%20but%20a%20resurgent%20AAP%20in%20the%20national%20sweepstakes.%20The%20regional%20parties%20have%20virtually%20obliterated%20the%20Congress%20in%20several%20states%20like%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Bengal%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20etc.%20But%20the%20party%20still%20had%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20make%20a%20comeback.%20It%20needed%20a%20big%20idea.%20It%20needed%20a%20booster%20shot.%20And%20yet%2C%20ironically%20enough%2C%20anyone%20who%20wrote%20off%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20did%20so%20at%20great%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMyth%202%3A%20The%20BJP%20will%20lose%20on%20anti-incumbency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20above%20has%20been%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20boogeyman%20and%20has%20revealed%20its%20myopic%20underestimation%20of%20its%20rivals%E2%80%99%20doggedness.%20Firstly%2C%20the%20BJP%20is%20a%20ruthlessly%20efficient%20machine%20whose%20immoral%2C%20yet%20pugnacious%20attitude%20permeated%20through%20its%20organisational%20core.%20It%20had%20overcome%20several%20headwinds%20with%20aggressive%20campaigning%2C%20using%20an%20adroit%20mix%20of%20falsehoods%2C%20social%20polarisation%20and%20exaggerated%20successes%20sold%20over%20WhatsApp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20on%20the%20WHO%20estimates%20of%20Covid%20deaths%20in%20India%20being%20allegedly%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20highest%20at%2047%20lakh%20people%2C%20the%20BJP%20flattened%20the%20Congress%20instead%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20being%20part%20of%20a%20Western%20global%20conspiracy%20to%20malign%20India.%20It%20was%20absolutely%20ridiculous%2C%20but%20the%20Congress%20response%20was%20typically%20tepid.%20Secondly%2C%20anti-incumbency%20works%20more%20in%20two-party%20Western%20democracies%20like%20the%20US%20or%20UK%2C%20where%20there%20is%20always%20a%20visible%20and%20viable%20alternative%2C%20tried%20and%20trusted%2C%20on%20the%20national%20mainstream.%20Margaret%20Thatcher%2C%20Tony%20Blair%2C%20Bill%20Clinton%2C%20Ronald%20Reagan%2C%20George%20Bush%20Jr%20had%20great%20runs%20that%20were%20abruptly%20terminated%2C%20because%20there%20was%20one%20clear%20option%20available.%20But%20in%20a%20multi-party%2C%20first-past-the-post%20system%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20beneficiaries%20of%20anti-incumbency%20through%20a%20splitting%20of%20votes%2C%20which%20neutralises%20the%20losses%20of%20the%20front%20runner%20Congress%20is%20waiting%20for%20Godot%20if%20it%20expects%20the%20BJP%20to%20just%20crumble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMyth%203%3A%20The%20Congress%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20default%20operating%20system.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20Jaipur%20address%20in%202013%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20made%20a%20forthright%20disclosure%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20we%20win%20elections%2C%20but%20we%20do.%E2%80%9D%20Everyone%20guffawed%2C%20but%20they%20had%20misunderstood%20what%20was%20a%20loaded%20confession.%20Rahul%20had%20correctly%20identified%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20messy%20organisational%20functioning%2C%20a%20chaotic%20muddle%20despite%20electoral%20winnings%2C%20but%20unfortunately%2C%20he%20did%20not%20fix%20it.%20The%20problem%20was%20in%20the%20execution%20bug.%20Just%20like%20how%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20hit%20the%20nail%20on%20the%20head%20in%201985%20at%20the%20Congress%20centenary%20celebrations%20when%20he%20said%20that%2085%25%20of%20one%20rupee%20was%20being%20appropriated%20by%20greedy%20middlemen%2C%20with%20only%20the%20balance%2015%25%20reaching%20the%20ultimate%20beneficiary.%20Rajiv%20too%20did%20not%20or%20could%20not%20rigorously%20execute%20a%20robust%20counter-plan.%20It%20would%20end%20up%20becoming%20an%20albatross%20round%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20neck%2C%20a%20perfect%20example%20of%20how%20the%20path%20to%20hell%20is%20paved%20with%20good%20intentions.%20The%20Congress%20is%20a%20victim%20of%20the%20false%20belief%20that%20it%20is%20the%20natural%20party%20of%20governance.%20India%20has%20of%20late%20begun%20experimenting%20with%20different%20kinds%20of%20software.%20Winning%20elections%2C%20managing%20the%20political%20brand%20and%20retaining%20public%20trust%20requires%20a%20solid%20operating%20plan%20in%20the%205G%20Age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Udaipur%20Declaration%20was%20important%3B%20it%20was%20an%20opportunity%20for%20renewal.%20The%20decision%20to%20rebut%20criticism%20of%20dynastic%20stranglehold%20by%20announcing%20a%20%E2%80%98one%20family%20one%20ticket%E2%80%99%20rule%20and%20the%20inclusion%20of%20%E2%80%98one%20person%20one%20post%E2%80%99%20augured%20well%20for%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20future.%20The%20Udaipur%20meet%20was%20a%20step%20forward%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%20But%20if%20the%20Congress%20believed%20that%20the%20status%20of%20the%20principal%20leadership%20of%20the%20Opposition%20that%20it%20occupied%20would%20be%20its%20sole%20prerogative%2C%20it%20was%20being%20presumptuous.%20There%20were%20others%2C%20more%20ambitious%20and%20adrenaline-pumping%2C%20who%20were%20eyeing%20the%20vacant%20space%20that%20the%20Congress%20had%20conceded%20generously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20political%20colloquialism%2C%20whenever%20there%20is%20a%20striking%20departure%20of%20a%20senior%20leader%20(such%20as%20Sunil%20Jakhar%20in%20Punjab)%20or%20a%20mass%20exodus%20(as%20in%20Meghalaya%20MLAs%20of%20Congress%20joining%20Trinamool%20Congress)%2C%20the%20clich%C3%A9%20uttered%20is%20%E2%80%98the%20rats%20are%20deserting%20a%20sinking%20ship%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20partially%20true%2C%20the%20capsizing%20Titanic%20part%20of%20it.%20But%20calling%20them%20rodents%20may%20be%20an%20exaggeration.%20In%20India%2C%20ideological%20fidelity%20is%20an%20oxymoron%3B%20it%20has%20become%20purely%20transactional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20in%20India%20is%20defined%20not%20by%20its%20love%20for%20free%20markets%20and%20less%20government%2C%20but%20by%20its%20religious%20doctrine%20of%20extreme%20Hindutva%2C%20national%20security%2C%20restorative%20nostalgia%20and%20nativism.%20The%20Left%2C%20for%20its%20voluble%20sympathy%20for%20Maoist%20rebels%2C%20anti-Americanism%2C%20antediluvian%20communist%20de-growth%20model%20and%20minority%20protection.%20That%20leaves%20the%20centre%2C%20which%20had%20become%20India%E2%80%99s%20default%20option%20under%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20inclusive%20political%20umbrella%20since%20Pandit%20Nehru%20became%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20although%20it%20was%20always%20Left-leaning.%20But%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20multiple%20regional%20parties%2C%20each%20doing%20a%20copycat%20manifesto%20pledging%20commitment%20to%20secularism%2C%20socialism%20and%20social%20justice%2C%20it%20has%20become%20a%20crowded%20square.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20full%20advantage%20of%20this%20ideological%20amorphousness%20was%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Mamata%20Banerjee.%20Her%20target%3A%20the%20severely%20depleted%20Congress%20party.%20The%20reason%20why%20many%20Congress%20leaders%20(L.%20Faleiro%2C%20Sushmita%20Dev%2C%20Kirti%20Azad%2C%20etc.)%20were%20merrily%20dancing%20to%20Didi%E2%80%99s%20drumbeat%20was%20because%20joining%20TMC%20was%20not%20causing%20a%20bitter%20heartburn%20unlike%20Congress%2C%20which%20was%20playing%20footsie%20with%20its%20%E2%80%98communal%20nemesis%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20BJP.%20Joining%20TMC%20was%20akin%20to%20leaving%20Facebook%20for%20WhatsApp%3B%20one%20was%20still%20part%20of%20the%20Metaverse.%20Banerjee%20was%20hoping%20that%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20market%20valuation%20would%20soon%20tip%20over%20that%20of%20the%20mothership%20itself.%20Her%20comment%20in%20Mumbai%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20no%20UPA%E2%80%9D%20(after%20meeting%20Sharad%20Pawar%20and%20Sanjay%20Raut)%20was%20a%20sardonic%20assault%20on%20the%20Congress.%20TMC%20was%20creating%20an%20alternative%20arrangement.%20It%20wanted%20to%20lead%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp-300x162.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp-1024x553.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683467%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22648%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWest%20Bengal%20chief%20minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40MamataOfficial%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Pawan%20Varma%2C%20former%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20called%20me%20and%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20private%20chat%2C%20I%20kind%20of%20figured%20out%20what%20he%20had%20in%20mind.%20Varma%2C%20who%20is%20an%20astute%20debater%20and%20a%20Stephanian%20wordsmith%2C%20did%20no%20pussyfooting%3B%20%E2%80%9CJoin%20the%20TMC%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20The%20Congress%20has%20become%20spiritless%2C%20limp%2C%20old%20fogey%2C%20was%20what%20he%20told%20me.%20TMC%2C%20under%20Mamata%20had%20the%20roar%20of%20a%20hungry%20tiger.%20TMC%20would%20be%20the%20new%20INC%3B%20a%20combative%2C%20strategic%2C%20streetfighter%20party%20that%20could%20defeat%20the%20BJP.%20The%20Goa%20assembly%20results%20would%20establish%20that%20paradigm.%20Verma%2C%20when%20he%20speaks%20in%20his%20deep%20baritone%20voice%2C%20making%20a%20persuasive%20argument%20which%20he%20considers%20ironclad%2C%20can%20even%20convince%20a%20lion%20to%20befriend%20a%20goat.%20I%20heard%20him%20out%20and%20promised%20to%20call%20him%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20was%20understandable%20that%20Congress%20targeted%20the%20BJP%20relentlessly%20given%20their%20historical%20rivalry%2C%20it%20made%20the%20cardinal%20mistake%20of%20underestimating%20its%20knavish%20allies%20or%20ex-Congressmen.%20It%20had%20ignored%20its%20own%20political%20history.%20The%20Jana%20Sangh%2FBJP%E2%80%99s%20meteoric%20rise%20began%20after%20the%20Congress%20was%20first%20damaged%20by%20non-BJP%20regional%20formations%3A%20The%20Janata%20Party%20in%201977%20(Jayaprakash%20Narayan)%2C%20V.P.%20Singh%20in%201989%2C%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20and%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%20following%20the%20Mandal%20agitations.%20The%20Mandal%20agitation%20damaged%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20support%20base.%20A%20bruised%20Congress%20then%20ceded%20substantial%20space%20to%20an%20industrious%20BJP%20which%20stepped%20up%20on%20aggressive%20majoritarianism%20using%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20agitation%20and%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20judgement%20to%20further%20cripple%20the%20slumbering%20centrist%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20larger%20RSS%20family%2C%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%2C%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20controversy%20came%20at%20an%20opportune%20time.%20Already%20facing%20heat%20from%20Muslim%20conservatives%2C%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%20now%20faced%20heat%20from%20Hindutva%20groups%20as%20well.%20The%20increasingly%20militant%20Hindutva%20groups%20got%20a%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20in%20February%20when%20the%20district%20court%20in%20Faizabad%20ordered%20the%20disputed%20site%20to%20be%20unlocked%20and%20allowed%20the%20public%20to%20pray%20at%20the%20spot.%20This%20seemingly%20small%20concession%20was%20to%20prove%20expensive%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETMC%E2%80%99s%20new%20outreach%2C%20which%20was%20curated%20by%20Prashant%20Kishor%2C%20was%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20Congress%20faced%20because%20of%20a%20serious%20internal%20erosion%20since%201989.TMC%20had%20an%20ambitious%20destination%3A%20to%20become%20the%20second%20largest%20political%20party%20(propelling%20Didi%20to%20become%20prime%20minister%20in%20a%20hung%20Parliament%20situation).%20Discerning%20observers%20would%20have%20noticed%20that%20it%20had%20already%20checkmated%20the%20BJP%20by%20doing%20a%20reverse%20migration%20of%20leaders%20back%20to%20the%20TMC%20after%20their%20hurricane%20sweep%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%20of%202022.%20At%20stake%20is%2042%20Lok%20Sabha%20(LS)%20seats%20in%20Bengal%3B%20the%20Congress%20has%2052%20LS%20seats%20pan-India.%20If%20the%20TMC%20swept%20Bengal%20and%20the%20Congress%20stagnated%20or%20dipped%2C%20anything%20was%20possible%3Cem%3E.%20The%20Economist%20%3C%2Fem%3E(it%20has%20endorsed%20Congress%20in%20practically%20every%20general%20election)%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20next%20general%20election%20is%20about%20three%20years%20away.%20It%20is%20not%20too%20late%20for%20Congress%20to%20become%20a%20big-tent%20national%20party%20capable%20of%20representing%20all%20Indians%2C%20as%20its%20founders%20intended.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKishor%20may%20have%20made%20one%20fatal%20miscalculation%20in%20his%20Operation%20Mamata%3A%20his%20assumption%20that%20the%20Congress%20would%20just%20wither%20away%2C%20succumbing%20meekly%20to%20his%20grandiose%20designs.%20He%20had%20on%20the%20contrary%20awakened%20the%20sleepy%2C%20somnolent%20giant.%20Two%20developments%20gave%20a%20hint%20of%20an%20unusually%20combative%20Congress.%20Firstly%2C%20the%20Congress%20promptly%20reassembled%20its%20traditional%20allies%20like%20DMK%2C%20National%20Conference%20and%20CPI(M)%2C%20in%20a%20quick%20bid%20to%20nip%20the%20TMC%20enterprise%20in%20the%20bud.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20joining%20them%20were%20also%20both%20NCP%20and%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20who%20had%20momentarily%20buoyed%20TMC%20hearts.%20Realpolitik%20is%20never%20linear.%20Congress%20President%20Sonia%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20not%20invite%20TMC%20even%20as%20a%20perfunctory%20gesture%20for%20a%20dinner%20meeting%20at%20her%20home%20was%20a%20declaration%20of%20war.%20Secondly%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20threw%20a%20curveball%20at%20the%20BJP%2C%20by%20belatedly%20biting%20the%20bullet%20on%20the%20Hinduism%20vs%20Hindutva%20debate.%20It%20is%20the%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%20that%20the%20Congress%20has%20imprudently%20dodged%20with%20disastrous%20results%20for%20too%20long.%20It%20showed%20a%20rare%20pragmatic%20risk-taking%20by%20the%20young%20Gandhi%20scion.%20Judging%20by%20initial%20reactions%20from%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%2C%20the%20BJP%20appeared%20threatened%2C%20at%20least%20temporarily.%20Rahul%20was%20still%20the%20only%20Opposition%20leader%20who%20made%20the%20BJP%20squirm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20assembly%20elections%20of%20early%202022%20in%20UP%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Goa%2C%20Manipur%20and%20Uttarakhand%20led%20to%20further%20decimation%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20it%20did%20not%20mean%20that%20TMC%20would%20find%20replacing%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20as%20main%20Opposition%20voice%2C%20a%20slam-dunk%20operation.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20Kishor%20had%20inadvertently%20rekindled%20the%20Congress.%20The%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Goa%20experiment%20was%20a%20complete%20fiasco%2C%20and%20with%20that%20brief%20flirtation%20with%20a%20pan-India%20power%20pitch%2C%20it%20abandoned%20its%20national%20aspirations%2C%20sticking%20to%20the%20more%20familiar%20Northeastern%20states.%20The%20BJP%20benefitted%20from%20the%20split%20votes.%20The%20Congress%20lost%20again%2C%20but%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20still%20hold%20on%20to%2024%25%20of%20the%20votes%20and%20get%2011%20seats%20in%20the%2040%20seats%20state%20assembly%20left%20no%20one%20in%20doubt%20as%20to%20who%20the%20real%20Congress%20was%2C%20warts%20and%20all%20had%20woken%20up%20at%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20did%20not%20call%20PawanVerma%20back.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20he%20expected%20me%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESanjay%20Jha%20is%20a%20former%20national%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20party.%20He%20also%20worked%20as%20a%20banker%20and%20an%20internet%20entrepreneur.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708160364000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195755%2FFvdM0YTWwAASRHL.jp