%2C%20Japan%2C%20once%20poised%20to%20become%20the%20world's%20largest%20economy%2C%20has%20also%20been%20struggling%20to%20recover%20after%20the%20Covid%20pandemic%20which%20crippled%20the%20country's%20finances.%20Japan%20has%20now%20slipped%20to%20the%20fourth%20position%20below%20Germany%20in%20the%20list%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGermany%20is%20already%20grappling%20with%20challenges%20in%20its%20export-dependent%20manufacturing%20sector%20and%20faces%20headwinds%20from%20soaring%20energy%20prices%20following%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20European%20Central%20Bank's%20decision%20to%20raise%20interest%20rates%20and%20uncertainties%20surrounding%20the%20budget%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20chronic%20shortage%20of%20skilled%20labor%2C%20further%20hamper%20Germany's%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spotlight%20has%20now%20turned%20on%20India%2C%20which%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20beacon%20of%20opportunity%20for%20investors.%20Projections%20from%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20suggest%20that%20India%20is%20poised%20to%20overtake%20both%20Japan%20and%20Germany%20in%20terms%20of%20economic%20output%2C%20with%20estimates%20placing%20the%20shift%20in%202026%20and%202027%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20remains%20the%20fastest-growing%20large%20economy%20and%20its%20growth%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%206.2%20per%20cent%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Economic%20Situation%20and%20Prospects%202024%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20currently%20the%20world's%20fifth-largest%20economy%2C%20placed%20behind%20the%20US%2C%20China%2C%20Japan%20and%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gross%20Domestic%20Product%20(GDP)%20of%20the%20US%20in%202023%20was%20%2427.94%20trillion%2C%20while%20China's%20was%20%2417.5%20trillion.%20India's%20GDP%20is%20about%20%243.7%20trillion%20but%20growing%20at%20a%20sizzling%20rate%20of%20around%207%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20benefiting%20from%20growing%20interest%20from%20multinationals%2C%20which%20see%20the%20country%20as%20a%20key%20alternative%20manufacturing%20base%20in%20the%20context%20of%20developed%20economies'%20supply%20chain%20diversification%20strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gap%20between%20developed%20countries%20and%20emerging%20nations%20is%20shrinking%2C%20with%20India%20now%20all%20set%20to%20capitalise%20on%20the%20opportunity%20to%20become%20a%20significant%20player%20in%20the%20global%20economic%20landscape.%20The%20shifting%20dynamics%20present%20a%20moment%20for%20India%20to%20assert%20its%20influence%20and%20contribute%20substantially%20to%20global%20growth%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708148580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2Fst7e19a_india-economy-manufacturing_625x300_09_November_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Findia-shines-as-worlds-top-economies-struggle-to-recover-after-covid-5074038%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20of%20the%20world's%20leading%20economies%20-%20Japan%20and%20the%20UK%20-%20recently%20entered%20into%20recession%2C%20highlighting%20the%20financial%20struggles%20that%20countries%20have%20been%20facing%20after%20the%20Covid%20pandemic.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Findia-shines-as-worlds-top-economies-struggle-to-recover-after-covid-5074038%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Findia-shines-as-worlds-top-economies-struggle-to-recover-after-covid-5074038%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Findia-shines-as-worlds-top-economies-struggle-to-recover-after-covid-5074038%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Is%20Sunetra%20Pawar%3F%20Buzz%20Over%20Ajit%20Pawar's%20Wife%20In%20Maharashtra%20Politics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%