l-5071985%5C%22%3E%20Alexei%20Navalny%3C%2Fa%3E%20died%20Friday%20in%20an%20Arctic%20Circle%20jail%2C%20the%20Russian%20prison%20service%20said.%20But%20his%20death%20is%20only%20the%20most%20recent%20of%20a%20long%20line%20of%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20critics%20who%20have%20been%20jailed%2C%20silenced%20or%20met%20brutal%20ends%20over%20the%20years.%20From%20plane%20crashes%2C%20accidental%20falls%20from%20windows%20to%20hangings%2C%20poisonings%20and%20health%20issues%2C%20many%20of%20the%20Russian%20President's%20critics%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20targeted%20in%20diverse%20ways.%20Many%20of%20the%20deaths%20are%20never%20solved%20and%20remain%20listed%20as%20accidental%20and%20suicides.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20some%20of%20the%20high-profile%20deaths%20involving%20those%20who%20have%20criticised%20the%20Russian%20leader%20over%20the%20years%20-%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYevgeny%20Prigozhin%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20head%20of%20the%20Wagner%20paramilitary%20group%20was%20once%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20most%20powerful%20oligarchs%20and%20a%20member%20of%20Mr%20Putin's%20trusted%20inner%20circle.%20He%20died%20in%202023%20at%20the%20age%20of%2062%20when%20the%20plane%20he%20was%20flying%20in%20exploded%20midair.%20Notably%2C%20the%20unexplained%20blast%20came%20two%20months%20after%20Mr%20Prigozhin%20led%20a%20failed%20mutiny%20against%20Russia's%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20over%20a%20disagreement%20with%20the%20direction%20of%20Moscow's%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20led%20a%20dramatic%20%26quot%3Bmarch%20for%20justice%26quot%3B%20where%20armed%20men%20were%20seen%20heading%20towards%20the%20Russian%20capital%20in%20June%202023.%20As%20Mr%20Putin%20remained%20silent%2C%20the%20mutiny%20was%20suddenly%20aborted.%20Mr%20Prigozhin%20ordered%20his%20troops%20to%20lay%20down%20their%20arms%2C%20before%20they%20were%20relocated%20to%20Belarus%20under%20a%20deal%20brokered%20by%20that%20country's%20Russia-allied%20president%2C%20Alexander%20Lukashenko.%20But%20two%20months%20later%2C%20Mr%20Prigozhin%20plummeted%20from%20the%20sky%20when%20the%20jet%20he%20was%20flying%20on%20from%20Moscow%20to%20St%20Petersburg%20apparently%20exploded.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKremlin%20critics%20and%20Western%20countries%20suggested%20foul%20play.%20However%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20denied%20any%20involvement%20in%20the%20downing%20of%20the%20aircraft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoris%20Nemtsov%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoris%20Nemtsov%2C%20a%20vocal%20Kremlin%20critic%20who%20was%20a%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20in%20the%20late%201990s%20under%20President%20Boris%20Yeltsin%2C%20was%20gunned%20down%20in%20February%202015%20on%20a%20bridge%20close%20to%20the%20Kremlin%20in%20Moscow.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F16%2Feurope%2Fputin-critics-dead-alexey-navalny-intl-cmd%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20had%20been%20arrested%20several%20times%20for%20speaking%20against%20Mr%20Putin's%20government.%20When%20he%20was%20killed%2C%20he%20was%20helping%20to%20set%20up%20a%20rally%20against%20the%20Russian%20military%20incursion%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20began%20in%202014%20with%20the%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20and%20the%20support%20of%20supposed%20separatists%20in%20the%20Donbas%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoris%20Berezovsky%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoris%20Berezovsky%20was%20once%20a%20powerful%20Russian%20businessman%20who%20fell%20out%20with%20the%20Kremlin%20and%20fled%20to%20England.%20He%20had%20accumulated%20his%20wealth%20following%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20A%20large%20chunk%20of%20his%20fortune%20came%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20luxury%20cars.%20But%20his%20wealth%20and%20political%20influence%20skyrocketed%20when%20he%20bought%20into%20Russian%20media.%20He%20relocated%20to%20Britain%20after%20losing%20favour%20with%20Mr%20Putin's%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20Mr%20Berezovsky%20was%20found%20dead%20on%20the%20bathroom%20floor%20of%20his%20UK%20home%20with%20a%20noose%20around%20his%20neck.%20British%20police%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20there%20were%20no%20signs%20of%20struggle%20and%20suggested%20that%20he%20had%20taken%20his%20own%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlexander%20Litvinenko%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Litvinenko%20was%20a%20former%20Russian%20spy%20turned%20Kremlin%20critic.%20A%20British%20inquiry%20determined%20Alexander%20Litvinenko%20had%20been%20poisoned%20at%20a%20London%20hotel%20bar%20in%202006%20by%20two%20Russian%20agents%20who%20spiked%20his%20green%20tea%20with%20the%20highly%20radioactive%20polonium-210%2C%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20Mr%20Litvinenko%20also%20always%20asserted%20that%20Mr%20Putin%20and%20the%20Kremlin%20were%20responsible%20for%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20always%20denied%20the%20accusation%20and%20has%20refused%20to%20extradite%20the%20two%20agents%20accused%20of%20the%20poisoning%20to%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERavil%20Maganov%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavil%20Maganov%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20board%20of%20Russia's%20second%20largest%20oil%20producer%20Lukoil%2C%20died%20six%20months%20after%20he%20openly%20criticised%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20He%20died%20after%20falling%20out%20of%20the%20window%20of%20a%20Moscow%20hospital.%20Russian%20state%20news%20agency%20%3Cem%3ETass%20%3C%2Fem%3Eclaimed%20his%20death%20was%20a%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnna%20Politkovskaya%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Politkovskaya%20was%20a%20vocal%20critic%20of%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Chechnya.%20She%20was%20gunned%20down%20in%20the%20entrance%20of%20her%20Moscow%20apartment%20in%20October%202006.%20Her%20death%20garnered%20international%20attention%20and%20it%20wasn't%20until%20June%202014%20that%20five%20men%20were%20sentenced%20for%20the%20killing%2C%20but%20it%20remains%20unclear%20who%20ordered%20the%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20shortly%20after%20her%20death%2C%20Mr%20Putin%20denied%20any%20Kremlin%20involvement%20in%20her%20killing%2C%20saying%20that%20Ms%20Politkovskaya's%20%26quot%3Bdeath%20in%20itself%20is%20more%20damaging%20to%20the%20current%20authorities%20both%20in%20Russia%20and%20the%20Chechen%20Republic%20...%20than%20her%20activities%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESergei%20Magnitsky%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESergei%20Magnitsky%2C%20a%20Russian%20tax%20adviser%20who%20exposed%20corruption%2C%20was%20detained%20without%20a%20trial%20and%20died%20in%20prison%20just%20seven%20days%20before%20he%20was%20set%20to%20be%20released.%20He%20was%20arrested%20in%202008%20and%20died%20on%2016%20November%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlexander%20Perepilichnyy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Perepilichnyy%20was%20a%20financier%20who%20became%20a%20whistleblower%20in%202010%20when%20he%20handed%20over%20files%20to%20Swiss%20officials%20showing%20details%20of%20the%20%24230%20million%20theft%20of%20funds%20from%20the%20Russian%20treasury.%20He%20died%20during%20a%20jog%20close%20to%20London%20in%202012%20after%20leaving%20Russia%20in%202009.%20While%20he%20was%20found%20to%20probably%20have%20died%20of%20natural%20causes%2C%20there%20are%20allegations%20that%20he%20was%20poisoned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20people%20mentioned%20above%2C%20at%20least%2013%20high-profile%20Russian%20businessmen%20have%20reportedly%20died%20by%20suicide%20or%20in%20mysterious%20circumstances%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708147800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fab6qiv58_putin-reuters_625x300_06_October_23.jp