%20Response%20to%20Its%20Recommendations%20on%20Citizens%E2%80%99%20Data%2C%20Privacy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F25143729%2Fdata-protection-1200x600.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IT%20Standing%20Committee%20has%20released%20its%2055th%20report%20reviewing%20action%20taken%20by%20MeitY%20on%20the%20observations%20and%20recommendations%20the%20Committee%20made%20in%20its%2048th%20Report%20on%20%E2%80%98Citizens%E2%80%99%20Data%20Security%20And%20Privacy%E2%80%99.%20It%20covers%20issues%20with%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20and%20Rules%2C%20their%20effect%20on%20IT%20Act%2C%20their%20consent%20framework%2C%20broad%20exemptions%2C%20and%20excessive%20rule-making.%20It%20urges%20MeitY%20to%20expedite%20passage%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Rules%20and%20%E2%80%9CDIA%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20we%20review%20these%20recommendations%20and%20urge%20MeitY%20to%20place%20meaningful%20public%20consultations%20and%20deep%20research%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20lawmaking.%20The%20blog%20includes%20excerpts%20from%20the%20reports%2C%20IFF%E2%80%99s%20past%20analysis%20on%20these%20issues%2C%20and%20naturally%2C%20some%20Taylor%20Swift%20songs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%C2%A0anyway%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20extended%20arm%20of%20the%20legislative%2C%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committees%20(%E2%80%9CPSC%E2%80%9D)%20(which%20include%20departmentally%20related%20standing%20Committees%2C%20finance%20Committees%20and%20administration%20Committees)%20keep%20a%20check%20on%20parliamentary%20affairs%20and%20give%20recommendations%20on%20complex%20law-policy%20issues%20to%20aid%20policy-making%20and%20reform.%20While%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20work%20gets%20done%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20for%20the%20legislative%20to%20scrutinise%20all%20ongoing%20government%20activities%20during%20short%20parliamentary%20sessions.%20PSCs%20were%20constituted%20to%20ease%20this%20burden%20by%20reviewing%20and%20issuing%20detailed%20observations%20and%20recommendations%20on%20proposed%20legislation%2C%20government%20policies%2C%20the%20legal%20environment%2C%20and%20union%20accounts%20and%20expenditure.%20Each%20Committee%20has%20a%20systematic%20deliberation%20process%20wherein%20they%20can%20invite%20inputs%20from%20experts%20and%20stakeholders%2C%20and%20even%20publish%20dissenting%20opinions%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20composite%20reports.%20Read%20more%20about%20the%20role%20of%20PSCs%20in%20legislative%20processes%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fparliament%2Fdiscussion_papers%2FParliamentary%2520Committees%2520Increasing%2520their%2520effectiveness.pdf%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehere%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20examining%20certain%20laws%2C%20policies%20or%20issues%2C%20PSCs%20come%20up%20with%20a%20consolidated%20report%20and%20table%20them%20in%20the%20parliament.%20Subsequently%2C%20they%20also%20submit%20Action%20Taken%20Reports%20which%20show%20how%20many%20of%20their%20recommendations%20have%20been%20accepted%20by%20the%20government%2C%20and%20the%20progress%20made%20on%20them.%20The%20report%20being%20analysed%20in%20this%20blog%20is%20one%20such%20action%20taken%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIT%20Committee%E2%80%99s%2055th%20Report%3A%20a%20list%20of%C2%A0would%E2%80%99ve%2C%20could%E2%80%99ve%2C%20should%E2%80%99ves%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2008%2C%202024%2C%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Communications%20and%20IT%20(%E2%80%9CCommittee%E2%80%9D)%20published%20its%2055th%20report%2C%20reviewing%20the%20action%20taken%20by%20the%20government%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20IT%20(%E2%80%9CMeitY%E2%80%9D)%20on%20the%20observations%20and%20recommendations%20the%20Committee%20made%20in%20its%2048th%20Report%20(dated%20August%2001%2C%202023)%20on%20%E2%80%98Citizens%E2%80%99%20Data%20Security%20And%20Privacy%E2%80%99.%20Reports%20of%20the%20Committee%20can%20be%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsansad.in%2Fls%2Fcommittee%2Fdepartmentally-related-standing-committees%2F18-communications%2520and%2520information%2520technology-nameH%3D%25E0%25A4%25B8%25E0%25A4%2582%25E0%25A4%259A%25E0%25A4%25BE%25E0%25A4%25B0%2520%25E0%25A4%2594%25E0%25A4%25B0%2520%25E0%25A4%25B8%25E0%25A5%2582%25E0%25A4%259A%25E0%25A4%25A8%25E0%25A4%25BE%2520%25E0%25A4%25AA%25E0%25A5%258D%25E0%25A4%25B0%25E0%25A5%258C%25E0%25A4%25A6%25E0%25A5%258D%25E0%25A4%25AF%25E0%25A5%258B%25E0%25A4%2597%25E0%25A4%25BF%25E0%25A4%2595%25E0%25A5%2580%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eread%20here%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20original%20report%2C%20which%20predates%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20(%E2%80%9CDPDP%E2%80%9D)%20Act%2C%202023%20in%20its%20current%20form%20by%20a%20mere%2010%20days%2C%20the%20Committee%20raised%20a%20list%20of%20concerns%20to%20MeitY%20on%20the%20rising%20risk%20of%20misuse%20of%20personal%20data%20and%20outdated%20provisions%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(%E2%80%9CIT%E2%80%9D)%20Act%2C%202000%2C%20highlighting%20that%20a%20data%20protection%20law%20must%20be%20urgently%20introduced%2C%20and%20citizen%20awareness%20and%20empowerment%20in%20data%20security%20should%20be%20prioritised.%20One%20member%20of%20the%20Committee%20submitted%20a%20dissent%20note%20regarding%20the%20rule%20making%20powers%20of%20the%20central%20government%2C%20exemptions%20to%20government%20agencies%2C%20and%20non-inclusion%20of%20non-personal%20data.%20MeitY%20has%20since%20submitted%20action%20taken%20notes%20to%20the%20Committee%2C%20responding%20to%20its%20recommendations%20and%20submitting%20updates%20on%20if%20they%20have%20been%20accepted%20or%20followed.%20In%20this%20report%2C%20published%20on%20February%2008%2C%202024%2C%20the%20Committee%20reviews%20MeitY%E2%80%99s%20action%20taken%20notes%20and%20further%20urges%20the%20Ministry%20to%20adopt%20its%20recommendations%20on%20certain%20pressing%20themes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-law-raises-questions-about-consistency-with-right-to-privacy-ruling%5C%22%3EDigital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Law%20Raises%20Questions%20About%20Consistency%20With%20Right%20to%20Privacy%20Ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiving%20into%20the%20report%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20we%20break%20down%20what%20the%20Committee%20said%20about%20actions%20taken%20by%20MeitY%20so%20far%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20DPDP%20Act%3A%C2%A0not%20a%20lot%20going%20on%20at%20the%20moment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20passed%20its%20original%20report%20before%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20current%20DPDP%20Act%20in%20the%20parliament.%20Many%20of%20its%20recommendations%20on%20the%20data%20protection%20environment%20predate%20the%20Act%2C%20but%20principally%20still%20hold%20some%20value.%20On%20provisions%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20relating%20to%20consent%20mechanisms%20and%20notice%20requirements%2C%20the%20Committee%20reiterated%20the%20importance%20of%20providing%20consent%20and%20notice%20in%20languages%20specified%20in%20the%20Eighth%20Schedule%20to%20the%20Constitution%20to%20ensure%20accessibility%2C%20clarity%20and%20comprehension.%20The%20Committee%20further%20noted%20that%20the%20default%20consent%20settings%20under%20the%20Act%20should%20be%20designed%20to%20extend%20benefits%20to%20data%20principals%2C%20especially%20those%20with%20low%20levels%20of%20digital%20literacy.%20For%20this%2C%20the%20Committee%20suggests%20MeitY%20can%20incorporate%20visual%20elements%20for%20consent%20and%20notice%2C%20promoting%20easier%20understanding%2C%20accessibility%2C%20and%20inclusive%20digital%20access%20while%20defining%20the%20prescribed%20methods%20for%20obtaining%20consent%20and%20delivering%20notices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20the%20Ministry%20responded%20that%20has%20noted%20the%20suggestions%20and%20is%20taking%20steps%20to%20ensure%20they%20reflect%20in%20the%20Act%20through%20the%20DPDP%20Rules.%20The%20Committee%2C%20unsatisfied%20with%20the%20response%2C%20noted%20that%20MeitY%20has%20not%20furnished%20any%20information%20on%20the%20present%20status%20of%20this%20action%20and%20merely%20parroted%20what%20the%20Committee%20suggested%2C%20and%20urged%20urgent%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20issue%20raised%20by%20the%20Committee%20on%20provisions%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20is%20the%20%E2%80%98deemed%20consent%E2%80%99%20clause%2C%20which%20was%20present%20in%20the%20draft%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%202022%20and%20has%20since%20been%20removed%20based%20on%20public%20consultation%20and%20feedback%20from%20stakeholders.%20Instead%20now%2C%20under%20the%20DPDP%20Act%2C%20personal%20data%20can%20now%20only%20be%20processed%20without%20consent%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20certain%20legitimate%20uses%E2%80%9D.%20The%20exemptions%20listed%20in%20Section%207%20are%20limited%20to%20the%20State%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20to%20%E2%80%9Cperform%20functions%20under%20law%20or%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%20and%20security%20of%20the%20State%2C%20to%20provide%20or%20issue%20subsidies%2C%20benefits%2C%20services%2C%20certificates%2C%20licences%20and%20permits%20that%20are%20prescribed%20through%20rules%2C%20to%20comply%20with%20any%20judgement%20or%20order%20under%20law%2C%20to%20protect%20or%20assist%20or%20provide%20service%20in%20a%20medical%20or%20health%20emergency%2C%20disaster%20situation%20or%20maintain%20public%20order%20and%20in%20relation%20to%20an%20employee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20original%20report%2C%20the%20Committee%20expressed%20concerns%20that%20there%20is%20still%20a%20possibility%20of%20these%20exceptions%20being%20misused%2C%20and%20strongly%20recommended%20the%20Ministry%20to%20devise%20a%20mechanism%20to%20ensure%20that%20these%20exceptions%20%E2%80%9Cdo%20not%20become%20the%20general%20rule%20and%20are%20used%20only%20in%20exceptional%20circumstances%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20promoting%20ease%20of%20living%20and%20the%20digital%20economy.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20this%20was%20evasive%20and%20vague.%20It%20listed%20Section%207%20requirements%20again%2C%20said%20it%20%E2%80%9Cis%20aware%E2%80%9D%20that%20it%20can%20be%20misused%E2%80%A6%20and%20said%20nothing%20else.%20The%20Committee%20notes%20this%20in%20the%20current%20report%20and%20again%20strongly%20urges%20MeitY%20to%20act%20and%20update%20them%20about%20their%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20is%20a%20vague%20and%20broad%20exemptions%20clause%20in%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20dangerous%20in%20its%20current%20form%2C%20the%20rule-making%20powers%20conferred%20to%20the%20executive%20by%20the%20Act%20as%20a%20whole%20makes%20it%20a%20tool%20for%20potential%20misuse%20as%20well.%20The%20union%20reserves%20the%20right%20to%20exempt%20any%20of%20its%20department%20or%20a%20third%20private%20party%20it%20is%20contracting%20with%2C%20from%20consent%20provisions%20under%20the%20Act.%20If%20this%20is%20the%20case%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20strong%20and%20expansive%20consent%20and%20other%20rights%20framework%20is%20under%20the%20data%20protection%20legislation%2C%20overbroad%20executive%20control%20and%20excessive%20future%20lawmaking%20powers%20can%20eventually%20render%20it%20meaningless.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20meaningfully%20engage%20with%20and%20analyse%20provisions%20of%20the%20Act%2C%20because%20it%20has%20not%20been%20enacted%20and%20remains%20to%20be%20operationalised%20through%20Rules%20(coming%20soon%3F).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20DPDP%20Rules%3A%20Death%20by%20a%20thousand%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9Ds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20original%20report%2C%20one%20of%20the%20many%20concerns%20on%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20that%20the%20Committee%20noted%20was%20the%20rule-making%20powers%20it%20confers%20on%20the%20union%20government.%20While%20the%20digital%20landscape%20remains%20dynamic%20and%20ever-evolving%2C%20it%20noted%20that%20rule-making%20powers%20must%20be%20used%20judiciously%20and%20with%20utmost%20care%20and%20responsibility%20by%20MeitY.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20Ministry%20assured%20the%20Committee%20that%20rule-making%20powers%20were%20a%20routine%20part%20of%20policymaking%20and%20necessary%20to%20make%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Act%20practical%20and%20feasible%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%2C%20unsatisfied%20with%20MeitY%E2%80%99s%20response%2C%20reiterated%20the%20need%20for%20responsible%20and%20judicious%20use%20of%20rule-making%20powers%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20rules%20formulated%20must%20be%20presented%20to%20the%20Parliament%20for%20scrutiny%20and%20discussion.%20It%20noted%20that%20the%20Ministry%20has%20merely%20outlined%20the%20established%20practice%20for%20rule-making%20without%20providing%20clarity%20on%20when%20the%20DPDP%20Rules%20will%20be%20finalised.%20According%20to%20established%20norms%2C%20it%20stated%2C%20rules%20under%20an%20Act%20should%20be%20framed%20within%20six%20months%20of%20its%20commencement.%20Since%20the%20data%20protection%20law%20was%20notified%20on%20August%2011%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Committee%20expects%20that%20the%20Rules%20in%20this%20regard%20should%20be%20nearing%20completion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20further%20believes%20that%20the%20lack%20of%20properly%20framed%20rules%20has%20prevented%20the%20notification%20of%20essential%20components%20of%20the%20data%20privacy%20law%2C%20including%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%2C%20which%20is%20mandated%20to%20investigate%20privacy%20breaches%20and%20impose%20penalties%20as%20outlined%20in%20the%20Act.%20It%20urged%20the%20Ministry%20to%20prioritise%20the%20finalisation%20and%20introduction%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Rules%20within%20the%20prescribed%20period%20of%20six%20months%2C%20and%20avoid%20seeking%20an%20extension%20on%20this%20front.%20It%20added%20that%20the%20rules%20drawn%20up%20must%20be%20simple%20and%20easy%20to%20understand%20and%20administer.%20The%20Committee%20asked%20to%20be%20informed%20of%20the%20efficacious%20steps%20taken%20by%20MeitY%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20DPDP%20Act%2C%202023%20lists%2025%20specific%20situations%20for%20which%20the%20union%20government%20will%20notify%20rules%20at%20a%20later%20stage%20and%20also%20gives%20itself%20the%20leeway%20to%20notify%20rules%20at%20a%20later%20stage%20for%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eany%20other%20matter%20which%20is%20to%20be%20or%20may%20be%20prescribed%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Such%20excessive%20rule-making%20has%20severely%20limited%20the%20ability%20of%20stakeholders%20to%20meaningfully%20engage%20with%20the%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%202022%20and%20Act%2C%202023%2C%20and%20for%20data%20principals%20and%20fiduciaries%20to%20understand%20and%20prepare%20for%20how%20the%20legislation%20will%20impact%20their%20rights%2C%20obligations%2C%20and%20conduct%20of%20business.%20While%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20procedures%20and%20specificities%20have%20to%20be%20left%20on%20future%20rule-making%2C%20these%20must%20not%20completely%20hamper%20the%20operationalisation%20of%20the%20parent%20law%20and%20must%20be%20accompanied%20by%20relevant%20safeguards%20to%20protect%20against%20arbitrary%20rule-making.%20The%20DPDP%20Act%20has%20not%20been%20enacted%20yet%2C%20and%20several%20of%20its%20procedures%20including%20on%20consent%20mechanisms%20and%20setting%20up%20of%20the%20statutory%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20cannot%20be%20operationalised%20without%20notifying%20specific%20rules.%20We%20agree%20with%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20about%20the%20overreliance%20on%20rule-making%20and%20the%20need%20to%20use%20these%20powers%20responsibly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20agree%20that%20the%20rules%20thus%20drafted%20must%20be%20simply%20written%20and%20easy%20to%20understand%20and%20administer%2C%20without%20compromising%20their%20substantive%20quality%20or%20scope.%20However%2C%20what%20causes%20some%20worry%20is%20the%20pressure%20from%20the%20Committee%20to%20expedite%20rule-making.%20Any%20legislative%20process%20must%20be%20preceded%20by%20extensive%20consultation%20with%20experts%2C%20civil%20society%20and%20the%20public%2C%20and%20must%20fall%20squarely%20within%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Though%20MeitY%20officials%20have%20indicated%20that%20the%20DPDP%20Rules%20will%20be%20put%20for%20public%20consultation%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fdraft-rules-under-privacy-law-almost-ready-it-minister-101698431489684.html%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enews%20reports%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0say%20that%20the%20time%20given%20for%20the%20public%20to%20respond%20will%20be%2045%20days.%20It%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20Ministry%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1TmwiMv_MSpZnkk-XljdJeln5f4WZcNPc%2Fview%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einvited%20feedback%20and%20public%20comments%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20the%20draft%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202022%20for%2030%20days.%20Where%20on%20one%20hand%20the%20Ministry%20provided%20stakeholders%20an%20entire%20month%20to%20send%20comments%20on%20a%20bill%20that%20was%20only%2024%20pages%20long%2C%20on%20the%20other%20it%20is%20considering%20a%20mere%2045-day%20public%20consultation%20period%20for%2021%20draft%20rules%20for%20a%20key%20piece%20of%20legislation.%20Further%2C%20some%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Fdata-privacy-rules-to-be-issued-for-consultation-shortly-rajeev-chandrasekhar-11703772692563.html%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enews%20reports%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0said%20they%20would%20be%20out%20before%20January%2031%2C%202024.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Ftechnology%2Fdata-protection-framework-postponed-dpdp-notifcation-after-lok-sabha-elections-18823331.htm%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESome%20say%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0not%20before%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20confusion%2C%20delays%2C%20and%20an%20inadequate%20consultation%20process%2C%20the%20DPDP%20Rules%20have%20a%20significant%20responsibility%20of%20operationalising%20the%20Act.%20Though%20deep%20research%20and%20nuance%20in%20lawmaking%20takes%20time%20and%20delays%20can%20be%20justified%20in%20certain%20circumstances%2C%20the%20contradicting%20statements%20from%20officials%20and%20rumours%20about%20a%20worryingly%20small%20consultation%20time%20frame%20are%20definite%20causes%20for%20concern.%20Thorough%20public%20consultation%20process%20forms%20the%20foundation%20of%20any%20democracy%20and%20is%20an%20effective%20means%20for%20the%20public%20to%20participate%20in%20policy-making%20and%20exercise%20their%20constitutional%20rights.%20MeitY%20must%20release%20the%20Rules%20for%20consultation%20with%20an%20ample%20time%20frame%20for%20the%20public%20to%20respond%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20%E2%80%9CDIA%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20original%20report%2C%20the%20committee%20%E2%80%9Cstrongly%20urged%E2%80%9D%20the%20Ministry%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Epromptly%20finalise%20the%20framework%20of%20the%20Digital%20India%20Bill%20and%20expedite%20its%20enactment%20without%20any%20undue%20delay%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20MeitY%20simply%20replied%20to%20this%20descriptive%20and%20long%20suggestion%20with%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221362%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flh7-us.googleusercontent.com%2FeYyFN0ja_tJwH7I1q6Wz7ecEG2Xv_2vXqiMGMZg1qGY_JjbZwX1jEeUHo7sK0Su-pVmv_QxQeUe57aWHFveyCQnsOS-b5VGkSUbjP35vSdXFtoF_DjWBYFDQu7f2004CyficZ1iHRiETgzlCcyqjVa8%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22206%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%2C%20understandably%2C%20reiterated%20its%20concerns%20more%20emphatically%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20outdated%20IT%20Act%2C%202000%2C%20which%20is%20now%2024%20years%20old%2C%20needs%20to%20immediately%20be%20replaced%20with%20a%20new%20%E2%80%9CDigital%20India%20Act%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9CDIA%E2%80%9D).%20The%20Committee%20urged%20the%20Ministry%20again%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Epromptly%20conclude%20the%20framework%20for%20the%20Digital%20India%20Bill%20and%20expedite%20its%20enactment%20without%20unnecessary%20delays%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20The%20curt%20response%20from%20MeitY%20did%20not%20help%2C%20as%20the%20report%20notes%20the%20lack%20of%20specified%20timelines%20for%20rolling%20out%20the%20%E2%80%9CDigital%20India%20Act%E2%80%9D%20and%20no%20indication%20of%20introducing%20it%20in%20the%20Budget%20Session%20of%20Parliament.%20The%20Committee%20notes%20that%20the%20Ministry%20has%20had%20ample%20time%20to%20release%20the%20draft%20bill%20for%20public%20consultation%20before%20its%20presentation%20in%20Parliament%2C%20but%20did%20not%20do%20so.%20The%20Committee%20reiterated%20the%20prompt%20action%20required%20and%20closed%20the%20review%20by%20stating%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ethe%20earliest%20action%20in%20this%20regard%20would%20be%20appreciated%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%9CDIA%E2%80%9D%20so%20far%20has%20been%20all%20bark%2C%20no%20bite.%20As%20we%20spoke%20about%20at%20length%20in%20our%20blog%20posts%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fdigital-india-bill-questions-unanswered%2F%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehere%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fmany-mysteries-of-the-digital-india-bill%2F%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehere%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MeitY%20officials%20have%20been%20talking%20to%20the%20media%20about%20the%20law%20at%20length%20and%20teasing%20its%20release%2C%20but%20no%20official%20notification%20or%20indication%20has%20come%20from%20the%20Ministry.%20As%20per%20media%20reports%20from%20May%202023%2C%20the%20consultation%20on%20the%20DIB%20was%20supposed%20to%20begin%20on%20June%207%2C%202023%20and%20the%20draft%20was%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Ftech%2Ftechnology%2Fdigital-india-bill-draft-post-consultation-to-be-ready-by-july%2Farticleshow%2F98524405.cms%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elikely%20to%20be%20ready%20by%20early%20July%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Then%20on%20June%2030%2C%202023%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelecom.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolicy%2Fdigital-india-act-draft-will-come-up-very-soon-chandrasekhar%2F101386593%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eadmitted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20delay%20in%20the%20release%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20and%20promised%20that%20it%20would%20be%20released%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20soon%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20believe%20that%20a%20clear%2C%20concrete%20timeline%20helps%20prepare%20stakeholders%20for%20a%20bill%20with%20such%20significance%20and%20alleviates%20a%20lot%20of%20mystery-led%20misery%20around%20the%20bill%2C%20we%20also%20consider%20deep%20consultations%20and%20consensus%20around%20the%20legislation%20from%20all%20stakeholders%20as%20equally%20important%20as%20the%20timelines%20by%20which%20the%20legislation%20is%20enacted.%20The%20only%20available%20resources%20include%20a%20powerpoint%20presentation%20shared%20by%20MeitY%20officials%2C%20which%20we%20have%20already%20performed%20post-mortem%20on%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fdigital-india-bill-questions-unanswered%2F%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20this%20blogpost%20here%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Several%20questions%20remain%20unanswered%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9CDIA%E2%80%9D%2C%20its%20ambitions%20and%20its%20mystery%20digital%20ecosystem%20%E2%80%9Creform%E2%80%9D.%20Until%20then%2C%20while%20we%20share%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20frustrations%20with%20still%20not%20having%20a%20law%2C%20we%20hope%20due%20process%20is%20followed%20by%20MeitY%20in%20opening%20it%20up%20for%20consultations%20and%20engaging%20with%20stakeholders%20more%20meaningfully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20IT%20Act%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20provisions%20of%20the%20two-decade%20old%20IT%20Act%2C%202000%20will%20become%20redundant%20with%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Act.%20The%20Committee%20noted%20that%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20will%20overhaul%20IT%20Act%20Sections%2043A%2C%2081%20and%2087%2C%20and%20also%20affect%20disclosure%20provisions%20under%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act.%20The%20Committee%20urged%20MeitY%20to%20proactively%20revisit%20the%20provisions%20of%20and%20notify%20amendments%20to%20all%20affected%20legislations%20and%20provisions%2C%20specifically%20in%20the%20IT%20Act.%20In%20response%2C%20MeitY%20noted%20the%20recommendation%20and%20listed%20the%20following%20amendments%20to%20the%20IT%20Act%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20removal%20of%20section%2043A.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20section%2081%2C%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Cor%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023%E2%80%9D%20after%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Patents%20Act%2C%201970%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20proviso.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20section%2087%2C%20the%20omission%20of%20sub-section%20(2)%2C%20clause%20(ob).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20seemed%20satisfied%20with%20MeitY%E2%80%99s%20response%2C%20but%20the%20reforms%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20undermine%20other%20digital%20rights%20and%20freedoms%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20IT%20Act.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20weakens%20the%20right%20to%20receive%20information%20from%20public%20authorities%20by%20removing%20the%20public%20interest%20exception%20to%20disclosure%20of%20personal%20information%20under%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%2C%20thereby%20diluting%20the%20Act.%20It%20further%20dilutes%20the%20scheme%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(Reasonable%20Security%20Practices%20and%20Procedures%20and%20Sensitive%20Personal%20Data%20or%20Information)%20Rules%202011%2C%20which%20accords%20a%20higher%20degree%20of%20protection%20to%20the%20processing%2C%20sharing%20and%20storing%20of%20sensitive%20personal%20data%20than%20other%20personally%20identifiable%20data%2C%20by%20removing%20the%20categorisation%20of%20%E2%80%9Csensitive%20personal%20data%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20itself.%20Such%20data%2C%20including%20health%2C%20sexuality%2C%20financial%20and%20biometric%20data%2C%20will%20now%20be%20processed%20with%20no%20more%20procedural%20requirements%20than%20data%20relating%20to%20home%20addresses%2C%20phone%20numbers%2C%20etc.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20many%20failures%20of%20the%20current%20DPDP%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeitY%2C%C2%A0are%20we%20out%20of%20the%20woods%20yet%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20of%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20are%20useful%20requests%2C%20we%20reiterate%20that%20MeitY%20must%20place%20meaningful%20public%20consultations%20and%20deep%20thematic%20research%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20lawmaking.%20Issues%20like%20consent%20and%20bridging%20the%20digital%20divide%20are%20complex%20and%20can%20benefit%20greatly%20from%20expert%20insights%20and%20stakeholder%20consultations.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9CDIA%E2%80%9D%20is%20chalk%20full%20of%20complicated%20themes%20and%20globally%20debated%20issues%2C%20so%20%E2%80%9Churrying%20up%E2%80%9D%20may%20not%20be%20solid%20advice.%20Instead%2C%20a%20comprehensive%20and%20well-thought%20out%20timeline%20for%20legislative%20processes%2C%20which%20is%20published%20by%20MeitY%20after%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20may%20be%20the%20better%20solution%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2F%5C%22%3Eofficial%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Read%20the%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fstanding-committee-action-taken-meity%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708092947000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F25143729%2Fdata-protection-1200x600.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fit-standing-committees-review-of-meitys-response-to-its-recommendations-on-citizens-data-privacy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20its%20report%20published%20last%20week%2C%20the%20Committee%20reviewed%20MeitY%E2%80%99s%20action%20taken%20notes%20and%20further%20urged%20the%20Ministry%20to%20adopt%20its%20recommendations%20on%20certain%20pressing%20themes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fit-standing-committees-review-of-meitys-response-to-its-recommendations-on-citizens-data-privacy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Navalny%20seen%20in%20video%20link%20a%20day%20before%20his%20reported%20death%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708092848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FC202%2Fproduction%2F_132666694_p0hccktp.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68319164%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russian%20opposition%20politician%20Alexei%20Navalny%20has%20died%20in%20jail%2C%20prison%20authorities%20say